<title type="html"><![CDATA[Putting 2 CPU (or PPU's) in a NES]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4366&amp;p=36867#p36867"><![CDATA[
It's not because the +5V pin of a chip is disconnected that the chip ceases to exists.<br />Most chips have diodes on input that does to +5V to prevent signals greatuer than +5V to disturb the inner mechanics of the chips. When the chip is not powered, but digitals signals are applied to it, it can be powered trough those diodes AND THIS IS A VERY BAD THING.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sat Sep 06, 2008 5:55 am</p><hr />
