<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4366&amp;p=36865#p36865"><![CDATA[
Hi!<br /><br />I was wondering if it was possible to fit both the PAL en NTSC CPU/PPU in a NES?<br /><br />The theory I had in mind was to cut or desolder the 5v pin from the board.<br />Solder a wire from the board to the middle leg of a switch.<br />a wire from the 5v pin of the PAL chip to one leg of the switch and from the other chip to the remaining leg on the switch.<br /><br />After that solder all the other legs of the floating chip to the right place on the board and see if it works.<br />And if it does, give the chip a nice place in the case.<br /><br />Will this work?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=877">downloader</a> — Sat Sep 06, 2008 5:03 am</p><hr />
